# Meta-Mind — Feature TODO
> A living document for proposed features, improvements, and design intentions.
> Add items freely. Expand into detail before implementation.

---

## [ ] 1. Fully Set Up Login / Sign-Up

**Intent:** Complete the Firebase Authentication integration so users can create accounts,
sign in, and have their data securely scoped to their identity.

**Details:**
- Implement email/password sign-up and sign-in flows via Firebase Auth SDK.
- Add Google OAuth as a one-click sign-in option.
- On first login, provision a default personal library and initial map for the new user.
- Replace the current local-storage-only persistence with Firestore, keyed to `uid`.
- The Profile Drawer (`#profile-drawer`) should reflect real user data:
  name, avatar, email, account tier, and sign-out button.
- Session state (active map, portal history) should survive page refresh for
  authenticated users (persisted to Firestore session doc).
- Protect all Firestore read/write paths with Security Rules scoped to `request.auth.uid`.
- Add an unauthenticated "guest" mode that works fully offline with local storage,
  with a clear prompt to save/sign-up before data is lost.
- Error states: show friendly inline messages for wrong password, unverified email,
  account-already-exists, network offline, etc.
- Forgot-password flow via Firebase `sendPasswordResetEmail`.

---

## [ ] 2. Update Data-Manager System to Project + Pages Architecture

**Intent:** Replace the flat library list in the Data Manager with a two-level hierarchy:
Projects (containers) and Pages (individual maps/sessions within a project).

**Details:**
- Introduce a `Project` schema: `{ project_id, meta: { title, description, icon, color },
  created_at, updated_at, page_ids[] }`.
- Each saved map (`map_id`) becomes a "Page" belonging to one Project.
- Data Manager UI redesign:
  - Left column: scrollable project list with creation/rename/delete controls.
  - Right column: pages within the selected project (card or list view, sortable).
  - "New Project" and "New Page" buttons with inline name entry.
- Portal destinations should be scoped/searched by project — allow cross-project linking
  but surface same-project pages first in the portal payload selector.
- Breadcrumb in the nav bar: `[Project Name] › [Page Name]` replacing the plain map title.
- Drag-and-drop to move a page between projects.
- Project-level export/import (zip of all page JSON files + project manifest).
- Firestore structure (when auth is live): `users/{uid}/projects/{project_id}/pages/{map_id}`.
- Migrate existing flat library entries to a default "My Project" project on first load
  after this change ships.

---

## [ ] 3. Refine Map UI — Auto-Collapse on Deep Downstream Nodes & During Highlighting

**Intent:** Reduce visual clutter in large maps by automatically collapsing nodes that
are far from the current focal point, and aggressively collapsing non-relevant branches
when a node is highlighted or selected.

**Details:**

### Auto-Collapse on Depth
- Define a configurable `autoCollapseDepth` (default: 3) in map settings.
- After any layout render, nodes beyond `autoCollapseDepth` hops from the focal/root
  node are rendered collapsed (their subtrees hidden) unless the user has explicitly
  expanded them.
- Expanding a deep node pushes its descendants' collapse threshold outward dynamically
  (lazy expansion pattern).
- Visual indicator on collapsed nodes: a badge showing child count (e.g. `+5`).

### Collapse During Highlighting / Selection
- When a node is selected or a search highlight is active, collapse all branches that
  do not lie on the path between the root and the selected/highlighted node(s).
- "Sibling" branches fade to 20% opacity rather than fully hiding, so the user retains
  spatial memory of the graph shape.
- Smooth CSS transition for collapse/expand so the map doesn't jump.
- An "Expand All" quick-action button (inspector or radial menu) to restore full view.
- Collapse state for selection-driven hiding is **ephemeral / view-only** — it is NOT
  written to `node.data.collapsed`. It is computed fresh on every render pass based on
  the current `selectedId`, so it never corrupts the stored map state.
- Permanent manual collapse (user explicitly collapses a node via the radial menu)
  continues to write to `node.data.collapsed` as before.

### Dynamic Auto-Re-Expansion on Selection Change
- When the user selects a **different** node, the map instantly re-evaluates which
  branches are relevant to the new focal point and re-expands them — no manual
  "Expand All" needed.
  - Re-expansion is driven by the same path-tracing logic used for collapse: compute
    the ancestor chain from root → new selection, plus the new node's immediate
    children (one level of look-ahead), and surface those branches.
  - Previously expanded siblings from the old selection are collapsed back automatically.
- When the user **deselects** a node (clicks empty canvas or presses `Escape`):
  - The map reverts to the **depth-based auto-collapse** view (`autoCollapseDepth`)
    rather than leaving whatever branches the last selection had opened.
  - This ensures the map always returns to a clean, low-clutter state when nothing
    is in focus.
- Selection changes and deselection both trigger a synchronous re-render (already
  done via `kernel.subscribe` → `render()`), so no extra event plumbing is needed —
  the collapse computation just needs to live inside `renderMap()` and key off
  `state.session.selectedId`.

### Polish
- Pinch-to-zoom and scroll-to-fit should account for the visible (non-collapsed) bounding
  box only.
- Keyboard shortcut: `C` to collapse selected node's subtree; `E` to expand.
- Transition timing: collapse/expand animations should complete in ≤ 150 ms so the
  map feels instant rather than sluggish on large graphs.

