## [ ] 4. Refine / Update Tutorial System — Reflect New Features & Ensure Auto-Nav

**Intent:** Bring the tutorial system up to date with all features added since initial
build (Person maps, portal save-on-exit, smart action button, type selector grouping,
phase engine visibility rules, etc.) and make tutorials drive the UI automatically
rather than requiring the user to navigate manually between steps.

**Details:**

### Content Updates
- **New tutorials needed:**
  - "Creating a Person Map" — person-root node, profile fields, child note auto-sync,
    Person phase engine view.
  - "Working with Portals" — creating a portal, linking to a library map, entering,
    editing the submap, exiting (with auto-save), the smart action button.
  - "Using the Smart Action Button" — context-sensitive actions per node type.
  - "Web Architect" — web-root map, node types (hero, section, card, footer),
    template application, Visual Editor phase view.
- **Update existing tutorials** to reflect renamed types (`person-root` vs old
  `user-profile`), new inspector type-selector grouping, and phase engine button
  visibility rules.

### Auto-Navigation
- Each tutorial step should be able to specify an `autoNav` field:
  ```json
  { "autoNav": { "view": "map" | "web" | "person" | "prompt" | "agent" } }
  ```
  When the tutorial advances to that step, `SC.setView(step.autoNav.view)` is called
  automatically.
- Steps can also specify `autoSelect: "<nodeId or nodeType>"` to auto-focus a node
  in the map.
- Steps should be able to highlight a specific DOM element with a pulsing ring overlay
  (tutorial spotlight) by specifying `spotlight: "<css-selector>"`.
- "Next" button in the tutorial panel should only activate once the user has completed
  the step's required action (e.g. added a node, changed a type), validated via a
  `validate` callback registered per step — or fall back to manual advance if no
  validator is defined.
- Tutorial progress persisted to localStorage so a refresh doesn't restart from step 1.
- "Restart Tutorial" button in the tutorial selection modal.

